    1.1 06.04.16 The LevelTwo class is a Level (JPanel) that contains all the setup for the third level of the game. It can be accessed by the user by going to menu, clicking on "Play", and choosing the "Medium" level.

    • Constructor Detail

      • LevelTwo

        public LevelTwo(int x,
                int y)
        The class constructor contains all the setup required for Level 2. Assigns appropriate values for Level 2 to variables inherited from Levels

        The volume is adjusted and the background music is started.

        Next, GameTimer is instantiated and the timer is started.

        In the for-loop, each element in the array, letters, is assigned a character from the chosen word.

        Then, in the next for-loop, the starting coordinates of the bubbles, their speed, and their angles are all determined randomly.

        The Levels class's instance variable, temp, is then assigned a value according to the first letter of the word chosen. Then, the method that plays the audio clip that plays the letter corresponding to the temp letter is started.

        Lastly, the background image is loaded in and startup() is called, which checks whether the user's input is correct or incorrect, and outputs the results accordingly.

        Parameters:
        x - int that stores the screen width
        y - int that stores the screen height
